<div id="content" lang="en" dir="ltr">
<a href="./RavenRed">RavenRed</a>: Just a minor idea, but perhaps at a certain level of Tidal Wave, you should get a direction prompt, which would allow the "wave" damage type. If this is aborted or targetted on the player, then the usual "ring" style is invoked.  <p>
<a href="./DarkGod">DarkGod</a>: How is a wave better than a ring ? I mean it covers less ground for the same damage. 
</p>
<p>
<a href="./RavenRed">RavenRed</a>: Pets for one thing. The other is that with the targettted ability, you can specifically push a segment of monsters away rather than a wholesale clearout.  
</p>
<p>
<a href="./MayLith">MayLith</a>: Increase damage for a directed wave? (See my water spell suggestions over on the forum.) 
</p>
